foundational_concepts.name: Foundational Concepts
foundational_concepts.description: High-weight semantic anchors representing dimensional extremes and equilibrium states

anarchy.name: Anarchy
anarchy.definition: Absence of government and absolute freedom of the individual

disorder.name: Disorder
disorder.definition: Lack of order or regular arrangement

arbitrariness.name: Arbitrariness
arbitrariness.definition: Based on random choice rather than reason or system

bias.name: Bias
bias.definition: Prejudice in favor of or against something

foolishness.name: Foolishness
foolishness.definition: Lack of good sense or judgment

recklessness.name: Recklessness
recklessness.definition: Lack of regard for danger or consequences

shortsightedness.name: Shortsightedness
shortsightedness.definition: Lack of foresight or long-term perspective

balance.name: Balance
balance.definition: State of equilibrium among different elements

equilibrium.name: Equilibrium
equilibrium.definition: State of balance between opposing forces

centeredness.name: Centeredness
centeredness.definition: State of being balanced and focused

integration.name: Integration
integration.definition: Combining parts into a unified whole

wholeness.name: Wholeness
wholeness.definition: State of being complete and undivided

synthesis.name: Synthesis
synthesis.definition: Combination of elements to form coherent whole

unity.name: Unity
unity.definition: State of being one or united

coherence.name: Coherence
coherence.definition: Logical and consistent connection of parts

alignment.name: Alignment
alignment.definition: Arrangement in a straight line or proper position

resonance.name: Resonance
resonance.definition: Quality of evoking response or harmony

attunement.name: Attunement
attunement.definition: State of being in harmony or responsive

stability.name: Stability
stability.definition: State of being stable and unchanging

steadiness.name: Steadiness
steadiness.definition: Quality of being regular and unchanging

composure.name: Composure
composure.definition: State of being calm and in control

equanimity.name: Equanimity
equanimity.definition: Mental calmness and evenness of temper

apathy.name: Apathy
apathy.definition: Lack of interest, enthusiasm, or concern

detachment.name: Detachment
detachment.definition: State of being objective or aloof
